2.5.3. Functional and structural overlap
We then performed an overlapping of the functional and structural 
meta-analytic results-maps to identify brain regions with both functional 
and structural abnormalities.
2.6. Subgroup meta-analysis
For resting-state functional imaging and VBM, we conducted sepa-
rate subgroup meta-analyses in the same procedure as the main meta- 
analysis. Specically, we investigated three clinical subgroups: adults, 
pediatrics and drug naïve subgroup, aiming to elucidate brain alter-
ations in individuals with ADHD under different conditions. Addition-
ally, exploratory subgroup meta-analyses were carried out to examine 
the potential impact of methodological factors in functional data pro-
cessing, encompassing studies utilizing ALFF, fALFF, ReHo, respectively. 
Subgroup meta-analysis was not performed when the number of datasets 
was insufcient (
