3.2. ADHD fMRI meta-analysis
Individuals with ADHD exhibited increased functional activity in the 
bilateral OFC and right parahippocampal gyrus compared to NCs. 
Conversely, there was observed decreased functional activity in the 
bilateral posterior cingulate cortex (PCC), and bilateral median cingu-
late cortex (MCC) extending to the anterior cingulate cortex/ medial 
prefrontal cortex (ACC/ mPFC) (see 
and 
for details).
